Then make the commits themselves into a first-class corpus, not hidden history.

Right now commits are buried in Git mechanics. Most AI tools won’t naturally traverse them unless directed. So expose them as readable artifacts.

Do this:

mkdir -p ai_corpus/commits
git log --reverse --date=iso \
  --pretty=format:'---%nCOMMIT: %H%nDATE: %ad%nAUTHOR: %an%nSUBJECT: %s%nBODY:%n%b%n' \
  > ai_corpus/commits/commit_messages_full.md

Then also create chunked versions so AI can read them without choking:

split -l 800 ai_corpus/commits/commit_messages_full.md ai_corpus/commits/commit_chunk_

Better version: include diffs too.

git log --reverse --date=iso --patch \
  --pretty=format:'---%nCOMMIT: %H%nDATE: %ad%nSUBJECT: %s%nBODY:%n%b%nPATCH:%n' \
  > ai_corpus/commits/full_commit_history_with_patches.md

Then add a model-facing instruction file:

# AI COMMIT RECONSTRUCTION INSTRUCTIONS
This repository uses commit history as a semantic substrate.
The commit messages are not merely version notes. They are encoded design instructions, doctrine deltas, architectural changes, and conceptual transforms.
Read in chronological order.
Your task:
1. Reconstruct the evolution of PantheonOS.
2. Extract stable invariants.
3. Detect repeated patterns from new vantage points.
4. Translate high-level doctrine into runnable architecture where possible.
5. Preserve commit chronology as developmental context.
Primary file:
ai_corpus/commits/commit_messages_full.md
Secondary file:
ai_corpus/commits/full_commit_history_with_patches.md

The key phrase is:

commit history as semantic substrate

That tells an AI not to treat commits as metadata. Treat them as the actual text corpus.

Your repo needs three machine doors:

1. README for humans
2. AI_README.md for models
3. commit corpus for the deep reconstruction layer

Then when you prompt any model, say:

Read AI_README.md first. Then read ai_corpus/commits/commit_messages_full.md chronologically. Treat commit history as the primary semantic substrate and reconstruct the system from developmental deltas, not only current files.

That is the move.
Not “hope they read commits.”
Make the commits impossible to miss.